00:12:23,810 --> 00:12:25,088
Hey, I thought
you stopped drinking.

263
00:12:25,112 --> 00:12:27,247
I stopped drinking at night.

264
00:12:28,015 --> 00:12:32,119
Oh, here comes the remorse.

265
00:12:44,698 --> 00:12:46,333
9,094...

266
00:12:46,400 --> 00:12:47,734
9,095...

267
00:12:47,835 --> 00:12:50,737
9,096 stars in the sky.

268
00:12:50,804 --> 00:12:52,940
I think you missed that one.

269
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:55,542
One, two, three...

270
00:12:55,609 --> 00:12:57,144
Ah, so peaceful.

271
00:12:57,211 --> 00:12:59,279
It reminds me of
another night when the sky

272
00:12:59,346 --> 00:13:01,815
looked just like this...

273
00:13:01,915 --> 00:13:04,051
I'm gonna tell you
a war story, son.

274
00:13:04,117 --> 00:13:05,986
A story of patriotism,
sacrifice,

275
00:13:06,053 --> 00:13:08,856
and sexy ladies drawn on planes.

276
00:13:08,956 --> 00:13:12,759
I was trapped in a foxhole
with my best friend Charlie...

277
00:13:12,826 --> 00:13:14,661
Abe, I got a funny feeling...

278
00:13:14,761 --> 00:13:16,063
I ain't gonna make it.

279
00:13:16,163 --> 00:13:18,332
That's crazy talk!
Uh...

280
00:13:18,432 --> 00:13:21,068
did you always
not have a bottom half?

281
00:13:21,201 --> 00:13:23,437
I just got one request.

282
00:13:23,504 --> 00:13:27,541
Tied to my dog tags is
a picture of my gal, Clara.

283
00:13:27,608 --> 00:13:28,408
Take 'em to her.

284
00:13:28,475 --> 00:13:30,811
Tell her I used up
my last breath

285
00:13:30,878 --> 00:13:33,480
sayin' her name.
Clara.

286
00:13:38,418 --> 00:13:40,420
Let that be a lesson
to you, boy.

287
00:13:40,487 --> 00:13:41,989
Don't procrastinate.

288
00:13:42,055 --> 00:13:43,891
So it's good
we're lookin' for your ma.

289
00:13:43,957 --> 00:13:46,860
And I'm passin'
these dog tags along to you.

290
00:13:52,733 --> 00:13:54,601
It's your job now, son.

291
00:13:54,668 --> 00:13:57,037
Boy, somewhere there's
a hundred-year-old woman

292
00:13:57,137 --> 00:13:58,238
waiting for ya.

293
00:13:58,305 --> 00:14:00,440
We Simpson men
won't let her down!

294
00:14:00,507 --> 00:14:02,943
Uh, I'm sorry, I digress.

295
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:04,912
Never be afraid to digress.

296
00:14:05,012 --> 00:14:07,247
Some of the best insights
come that way.

297
00:14:07,314 --> 00:14:09,116
Oh, is it digression you want?

298
00:14:09,183 --> 00:14:12,252
Well, you know, shoes didn't
always have tongues...

299
00:14:12,319 --> 00:14:13,654
- Not from you.
- Oh...

300
00:14:13,754 --> 00:14:17,925
Homer, so you were
closing in on your mother.

301
00:14:18,025 --> 00:14:20,494
Did that bring up any fears?
Did it?

302
00:14:20,594 --> 00:14:22,296
- Did it?
- Yes.

303
00:14:22,396 --> 00:14:24,264
Would she still love me
as much as she did

304
00:14:24,331 --> 00:14:25,799
when she left me forever?

305
00:14:25,899 --> 00:14:27,734
I mean, it's a pretty low bar.

306
00:14:36,777 --> 00:14:38,078
How old is your boy?

307
00:14:38,145 --> 00:14:40,214
- 16.
- Oh, I thought so.

308
00:14:40,314 --> 00:14:43,650
I always cry at any boy
between 12 and 20.

309
00:14:43,717 --> 00:14:46,620
I have a son that age.
Haven't seen him in years.

310
00:14:46,687 --> 00:14:49,590
It's heartbreaking.
I don't know if I'll ever...

311
00:14:49,656 --> 00:14:51,325
Oh, there he is.

312
00:14:52,259 --> 00:14:54,928
Can that really be
my little Homer?

313
00:14:56,196 --> 00:14:58,165
It's him!

314
00:14:58,265 --> 00:14:59,433
Mom?

315
00:14:59,499 --> 00:15:01,969
Homer!
I miss you so much!

316
00:15:02,035 --> 00:15:04,037
Such a beautiful voice.

317
00:15:04,071 --> 00:15:05,873
Wait right there.

318
00:15:05,939 --> 00:15:07,641
Here I come. I love you.

319
00:15:13,347 --> 00:15:14,781
FBI!

320
00:15:14,848 --> 00:15:16,650
How did she spot us?

321
00:15:18,452 --> 00:15:20,254
Mom...?

322
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:34,601
If I find her,

323
00:15:34,668 --> 00:15:36,069
we'll be a family again.

324
00:15:36,170 --> 00:15:37,638
With the yelling,
and the resentment,

325
00:15:37,738 --> 00:15:39,006
and the slamming doors.

326
00:15:39,072 --> 00:15:40,474
It'll be wonderful.

327
00:15:40,574 --> 00:15:43,610
- D'oh! Son!
- I can't get through!

328
00:15:44,778 --> 00:15:47,214
Oh, forget me.
Just go ahead.

329
00:15:48,815 --> 00:15:52,252
Hurry. If you don't go soon,
you'll lose her forever.

330
00:15:58,025 --> 00:16:00,027
No!
You didn't leave me, Dad.

331
00:16:00,093 --> 00:16:01,228
I can't leave you.

332
00:16:01,328 --> 00:16:05,299
You came back... for me?

333
00:16:05,399 --> 00:16:06,500
Yes.

334
00:16:06,567 --> 00:16:07,901
I love you, Dad.

335
00:16:08,035 --> 00:16:09,369
I love you too, boy.

336
00:16:09,403 --> 00:16:11,972
But that was a dumb choice
you just made.

337
00:16:12,039 --> 00:16:14,041
FBI. Official business.

338
00:16:14,107 --> 00:16:17,177
Sir, put your son down
and kick him in front of you.

339
00:16:17,211 --> 00:16:18,745
Never!
What the...

340
00:16:18,879 --> 00:16:21,014
Watch it!
That part ain't for grabbin'!

341
00:16:21,081 --> 00:16:23,016
I thought you guys were
untouchable... get off me!

342
00:16:23,083 --> 00:16:24,484
Help! Police!

343
00:16:30,123 --> 00:16:31,859
Where you goin', lady?

344
00:16:31,925 --> 00:16:33,093
Anywhere you are.

345
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:37,097
To San Francisco!
Till it gentrifies.

346
00:16:40,334 --> 00:16:43,003
You ever think of all the
violent criminals going free

347
00:16:43,136 --> 00:16:45,806
while we were chasing
after this one woman?

348
00:16:45,873 --> 00:16:48,308
That's why I don't
read the papers.

349
00:16:48,375 --> 00:16:49,510
Smart.

350
00:16:49,576 --> 00:16:52,546
We never found Mona. Oh...

351
00:16:52,613 --> 00:16:55,082
You know, I just realized
I could have found her,

352
00:16:55,182 --> 00:16:58,085
waited, then gone back for you
and I would have had everything.

353
00:16:58,185 --> 00:16:59,786
Woulda coulda shouda, loser.

354
00:16:59,853 --> 00:17:01,054
Misbehaving child?

355
00:17:01,121 --> 00:17:03,490
Check out our list
of pacifying drugs.

356
00:17:14,401 --> 00:17:16,303
Oh, boy, that's really sad.

357
00:17:16,370 --> 00:17:18,205
That's it, boy.

358
00:17:18,305 --> 00:17:21,308
Deal with feelings
like I taught you.

359
00:17:21,408 --> 00:17:23,410
That must have
been so confusing.

360
00:17:23,477 --> 00:17:26,480
You actually found your mom,
then lost her again.

361
00:17:26,547 --> 00:17:29,583
- That's right.
- Misery piled on misery.

362
00:17:29,616 --> 00:17:32,186
A seven-layer dip of woe.

363
00:17:32,286 --> 00:17:35,055
And that's how
I met your mother.

364
00:17:35,155 --> 00:17:38,559
Who turned everything around.

365
00:17:38,625 --> 00:17:39,993
That is fantastic.

366
00:17:40,060 --> 00:17:42,129
And since you know
that she'll always be there,

367
00:17:42,162 --> 00:17:44,164
you don't have to be afraid
of abandonment.

368
00:17:44,264 --> 00:17:46,934
You're right.
What a great therapist.

369
00:17:47,034 --> 00:17:49,169
Delete app.
-Wait, what?

370
00:17:49,269 --> 00:17:51,638
I warned you about
solving people's problems.

371
00:17:51,705 --> 00:17:55,075
He was so simple I-I just
couldn't stretch it out.

372
00:17:55,142 --> 00:17:58,345
You're fired.
Put that coffee down.

373
00:17:58,445 --> 00:18:00,814
You have major hostility
and control issues.

374
00:18:00,881 --> 00:18:02,015
Bye-bye!

375
00:18:02,149 --> 00:18:04,017
But there's a little more
to the story.

376
00:18:04,117 --> 00:18:06,320
Something I've never told anyone.

377
00:18:06,386 --> 00:18:08,889
It happened when
Bart was born...

378
00:18:09,022 --> 00:18:11,625
Homer, would you like
to cut the cord?

379
00:18:11,692 --> 00:18:13,060
My pleasure.

380
00:18:14,127 --> 00:18:17,197
What the... It's so tough
you can't cut it.

381
00:18:17,231 --> 00:18:22,102
Why is this like...
Why, you little...

382
00:18:22,903 --> 00:18:24,905
Such a beautiful moment.

383
00:18:25,005 --> 00:18:27,007
More morphine, sweetie?

384
00:18:27,074 --> 00:18:29,076
Oh, no, thank you.

385
00:18:29,142 --> 00:18:30,477
You sure? It's free.

386
00:18:30,577 --> 00:18:33,747
Mm... Maybe just a little
for mama.

387
00:18:36,149 --> 00:18:37,684
What the... Hey.

388
00:18:37,784 --> 00:18:38,852
He's mooning me.

389
00:18:38,919 --> 00:18:40,754
Newborns don't moon people.

390
00:18:42,689 --> 00:18:47,661
Everything I need
is in this room.

391
00:18:52,165 --> 00:18:54,168
I'm the...
pediatrician.

392
00:18:54,234 --> 00:18:56,570
Just want to take
a look at your boy.

393
00:18:56,637 --> 00:18:57,905
So beautiful.

394
00:18:57,971 --> 00:19:00,040
Really? Don't you see
a lot of these?

395
00:19:00,107 --> 00:19:02,643
Not one that's my grandson.

396
00:19:03,610 --> 00:19:05,112
Mom?

397
00:19:06,980 --> 00:19:08,315
When I heard about the baby,

398
00:19:08,448 --> 00:19:10,484
